properties.areaDesc: Waters from Cape Mendocino to Pt. Arena CA from 10 to 60 nm
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 16 at 8:38AM PST until February 18 at 3:00AM PST by NWS Eureka CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, north winds 25 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 40 kt and steep seas 11 to 13 feet expected. For
the Small Craft Advisory, north winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts
up to 35 kt and steep seas building to 8 to 10 feet expected.

* WHERE...Cape Mendocino to Pt Arena 10 to 60 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 3 PM Monday to 3 AM PST
Tuesday. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 7 PM this evening
to 3 PM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 3 PM PST MONDAY... ...GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM MONDAY TO 3 AM PST TUESDAY
